{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"So, I've known a lot of fish in my life."},{"time":5000,"text":"I've loved only two."},{"time":8000,"text":"That first one,"},{"time":10000,"text":"it was more like a passionate affair."},{"time":13000,"text":"It was a beautiful fish:"},{"time":15000,"text":"flavorful, textured, meaty,"},{"time":18000,"text":"a bestseller on the menu."},{"time":20000,"text":"What a fish."},{"time":22000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":25000,"text":"Even better,"},{"time":27000,"text":"it was farm-raised to the supposed highest standards"},{"time":30000,"text":"of sustainability."},{"time":33000,"text":"So you could feel good about selling it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"I was in a relationship with this beauty"},{"time":39000,"text":"for several months."},{"time":43000,"text":"One day, the head of the company called"},{"time":45000,"text":"and asked if I'd speak at an event"},{"time":47000,"text":"about the farm's sustainability."},{"time":49000,"text":"\"Absolutely,\" I said."},{"time":51000,"text":"Here was a company trying to solve"},{"time":54000,"text":"what's become this unimaginable problem for us chefs:"},{"time":58000,"text":"How do we keep fish on our menus?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":62000,"text":"For the past 50 years,"},{"time":65000,"text":"we've been fishing the seas"},{"time":67000,"text":"like we clear-cut forests."},{"time":70000,"text":"It's hard to overstate the destruction."},{"time":75000,"text":"Ninety percent of large fish, the ones we love --"},{"time":78000,"text":"the tunas, the halibuts, the salmons, swordfish --"},{"time":81000,"text":"they've collapsed."},{"time":83000,"text":"There's almost nothing left."},{"time":86000,"text":"So, for better or for worse,"},{"time":89000,"text":"aquaculture, fish farming, is going to be a part of our future."},{"time":92000,"text":"A lot of arguments against it:"},{"time":94000,"text":"Fish farms pollute -- most of them do anyway --"},{"time":97000,"text":"and they're inefficient. Take tuna,"},{"time":99000,"text":"a major drawback."},{"time":101000,"text":"It's got a feed conversion ratio"},{"time":103000,"text":"of 15 to one."},{"time":105000,"text":"That means it takes fifteen pounds of wild fish"},{"time":107000,"text":"to get you one pound of farm tuna."},{"time":111000,"text":"Not very sustainable."},{"time":113000,"text":"It doesn't taste very good either."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"So here, finally,"},{"time":118000,"text":"was a company trying to do it right."},{"time":120000,"text":"I wanted to support them."},{"time":123000,"text":"The day before the event,"},{"time":125000,"text":"I called the head of P.R. for the company."},{"time":128000,"text":"Let's call him Don."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132000,"text":"\"Don,\" I said, \"just to get the facts straight, you guys are famous"},{"time":135000,"text":"for farming so far out to sea, you don't pollute.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":138000,"text":"\"That's right,\" he said. \"We're so far out,"},{"time":141000,"text":"the waste from our fish gets distributed,"},{"time":144000,"text":"not concentrated.\""},{"time":146000,"text":"And then he added,"},{"time":148000,"text":"\"We're basically a world unto ourselves."},{"time":152000,"text":"That feed conversion ratio? 2.5 to one,\" he said."},{"time":155000,"text":"\"Best in the business.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":157000,"text":"2.5 to one, great."},{"time":159000,"text":"\"2.5 what? What are you feeding?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"\"Sustainable proteins,\" he said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164000,"text":"\"Great,\" I said. Got off the phone."},{"time":167000,"text":"And that night, I was lying in bed, and I thought:"},{"time":170000,"text":"What the hell is a sustainable protein?"},{"time":172000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":177000,"text":"So the next day, just before the event, I called Don."},{"time":179000,"text":"I said, \"Don, what are some examples of sustainable proteins?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":183000,"text":"He said he didn't know. He would ask around."},{"time":186000,"text":"Well, I got on the phone with a few people in the company;"},{"time":188000,"text":"no one could give me a straight answer"},{"time":191000,"text":"until finally, I got on the phone"},{"time":194000,"text":"with the head biologist."},{"time":196000,"text":"Let's call him Don too."},{"time":198000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":202000,"text":"\"Don,\" I said,"},{"time":204000,"text":"\"what are some examples of sustainable proteins?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"Well, he mentioned some algaes"},{"time":209000,"text":"and some fish meals,"},{"time":211000,"text":"and then he said chicken pellets."},{"time":213000,"text":"I said, \"Chicken pellets?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"He said, \"Yeah, feathers, skin,"},{"time":217000,"text":"bone meal, scraps,"},{"time":219000,"text":"dried and processed into feed.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":222000,"text":"I said, \"What percentage"},{"time":224000,"text":"of your feed is chicken?\""},{"time":227000,"text":"Thinking, you know, two percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230000,"text":"\"Well, it's about 30 percent,\" he said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233000,"text":"I said, \"Don, what's sustainable"},{"time":236000,"text":"about feeding chicken to fish?\""},{"time":238000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":243000,"text":"There was a long pause on the line,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and he said, \"There's just too much chicken in the world.\""},{"time":249000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":255000,"text":"I fell out of love with this fish."},{"time":257000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":259000,"text":"No, not because I'm some self-righteous,"},{"time":262000,"text":"goody-two shoes foodie."},{"time":264000,"text":"I actually am."},{"time":266000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":268000,"text":"No, I actually fell out of love with this fish because, I swear to God,"},{"time":270000,"text":"after that conversation, the fish tasted like chicken."},{"time":273000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"This second fish,"},{"time":286000,"text":"it's a different kind of love story."},{"time":289000,"text":"It's the romantic kind,"},{"time":292000,"text":"the kind where the more you get to know your fish,"},{"time":295000,"text":"you love the fish."},{"time":298000,"text":"I first ate it at a restaurant"},{"time":300000,"text":"in southern Spain."},{"time":302000,"text":"A journalist friend had been talking about this fish for a long time."},{"time":305000,"text":"She kind of set us up."},{"time":307000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":309000,"text":"It came to the table"},{"time":311000,"text":"a bright, almost shimmering, white color."},{"time":316000,"text":"The chef had overcooked it."},{"time":319000,"text":"Like twice over."},{"time":322000,"text":"Amazingly, it was still delicious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"Who can make a fish taste good"},{"time":329000,"text":"after it's been overcooked?"},{"time":331000,"text":"I can't,"},{"time":333000,"text":"but this guy can."},{"time":335000,"text":"Let's call him Miguel --"},{"time":337000,"text":"actually his name is Miguel."},{"time":339000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":342000,"text":"And no, he didn't cook the fish, and he's not a chef,"},{"time":344000,"text":"at least in the way that you and I understand it."},{"time":348000,"text":"He's a biologist"},{"time":350000,"text":"at Veta La Palma."},{"time":352000,"text":"It's a fish farm in the southwestern corner of Spain."},{"time":355000,"text":"It's at the tip of the Guadalquivir river."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358000,"text":"Until the 1980s,"},{"time":360000,"text":"the farm was in the hands of the Argentinians."},{"time":363000,"text":"They raised beef cattle"},{"time":365000,"text":"on what was essentially wetlands."},{"time":368000,"text":"They did it by draining the land."},{"time":370000,"text":"They built this intricate series of canals,"},{"time":373000,"text":"and they pushed water off the land and out into the river."},{"time":377000,"text":"Well, they couldn't make it work,"},{"time":379000,"text":"not economically."},{"time":381000,"text":"And ecologically, it was a disaster."},{"time":384000,"text":"It killed like 90 percent of the birds,"},{"time":386000,"text":"which, for this place, is a lot of birds."},{"time":389000,"text":"And so in 1982,"},{"time":391000,"text":"a Spanish company with an environmental conscience"},{"time":393000,"text":"purchased the land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"What did they do?"},{"time":397000,"text":"They reversed the flow of water."},{"time":399000,"text":"They literally flipped the switch."},{"time":401000,"text":"Instead of pushing water out,"},{"time":403000,"text":"they used the channels to pull water back in."},{"time":405000,"text":"They flooded the canals."},{"time":407000,"text":"They created a 27,000-acre fish farm --"},{"time":411000,"text":"bass, mullet,"},{"time":413000,"text":"shrimp, eel --"},{"time":416000,"text":"and in the process, Miguel and this company"},{"time":419000,"text":"completely reversed the ecological destruction."},{"time":423000,"text":"The farm's incredible."},{"time":425000,"text":"I mean, you've never seen anything like this."},{"time":428000,"text":"You stare out at a horizon"},{"time":431000,"text":"that is a million miles away,"},{"time":433000,"text":"and all you see are flooded canals"},{"time":435000,"text":"and this thick, rich marshland."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440000,"text":"I was there not long ago with Miguel."},{"time":443000,"text":"He's an amazing guy,"},{"time":446000,"text":"like three parts Charles Darwin and one part Crocodile Dundee."},{"time":449000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":451000,"text":"Okay? There we are slogging through the wetlands,"},{"time":455000,"text":"and I'm panting and sweating, got mud up to my knees,"},{"time":457000,"text":"and Miguel's calmly conducting a biology lecture."},{"time":461000,"text":"Here, he's pointing out a rare Black-shouldered Kite."},{"time":464000,"text":"Now, he's mentioning the mineral needs of phytoplankton."},{"time":468000,"text":"And here, here he sees a grouping pattern"},{"time":471000,"text":"that reminds him of the Tanzanian Giraffe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"It turns out, Miguel spent the better part of his career"},{"time":479000,"text":"in the Mikumi National Park in Africa."},{"time":482000,"text":"I asked him how he became"},{"time":484000,"text":"such an expert on fish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486000,"text":"He said, \"Fish? I didn't know anything about fish."},{"time":489000,"text":"I'm an expert in relationships.\""},{"time":492000,"text":"And then he's off, launching into more talk"},{"time":494000,"text":"about rare birds and algaes"},{"time":496000,"text":"and strange aquatic plants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498000,"text":"And don't get me wrong, that was really fascinating, you know,"},{"time":501000,"text":"the biotic community unplugged, kind of thing."},{"time":504000,"text":"It's great, but I was in love."},{"time":507000,"text":"And my head was swooning over that"},{"time":510000,"text":"overcooked piece of delicious fish I had the night before."},{"time":513000,"text":"So I interrupted him. I said,"},{"time":515000,"text":"\"Miguel, what makes your fish taste so good?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":517000,"text":"He pointed at the algae."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"\"I know, dude, the algae, the phytoplankton,"},{"time":522000,"text":"the relationships: It's amazing."},{"time":525000,"text":"But what are your fish eating?"},{"time":527000,"text":"What's the feed conversion ratio?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"Well, he goes on to tell me"},{"time":534000,"text":"it's such a rich system"},{"time":536000,"text":"that the fish are eating what they'd be eating in the wild."},{"time":539000,"text":"The plant biomass, the phytoplankton,"},{"time":542000,"text":"the zooplankton, it's what feeds the fish."},{"time":544000,"text":"The system is so healthy,"},{"time":546000,"text":"it's totally self-renewing."},{"time":548000,"text":"There is no feed."},{"time":551000,"text":"Ever heard of a farm that doesn't feed its animals?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":558000,"text":"Later that day, I was driving around this property with Miguel,"},{"time":560000,"text":"and I asked him, I said, \"For a place that seems so natural,"},{"time":564000,"text":"unlike like any farm I'd ever been at,"},{"time":569000,"text":"how do you measure success?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"At that moment, it was as if"},{"time":575000,"text":"a film director called for a set change."},{"time":577000,"text":"And we rounded the corner"},{"time":579000,"text":"and saw the most amazing sight:"},{"time":581000,"text":"thousands and thousands of pink flamingos,"},{"time":584000,"text":"a literal pink carpet for as far as you could see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588000,"text":"\"That's success,\" he said."},{"time":591000,"text":"\"Look at their bellies, pink."},{"time":593000,"text":"They're feasting.\""},{"time":595000,"text":"Feasting? I was totally confused."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597000,"text":"I said, \"Miguel, aren't they feasting on your fish?\""},{"time":599000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"\"Yes,\" he said."},{"time":603000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":609000,"text":"\"We lose 20 percent of our fish"},{"time":611000,"text":"and fish eggs to birds."},{"time":615000,"text":"Well, last year, this property"},{"time":617000,"text":"had 600,000 birds on it,"},{"time":619000,"text":"more than 250 different species."},{"time":621000,"text":"It's become, today, the largest"},{"time":624000,"text":"and one of the most important"},{"time":627000,"text":"private bird sanctuaries in all of Europe.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":631000,"text":"I said, \"Miguel, isn't a thriving bird population"},{"time":634000,"text":"like the last thing you want on a fish farm?\""},{"time":636000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":638000,"text":"He shook his head, no."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640000,"text":"He said, \"We farm extensively,"},{"time":643000,"text":"not intensively."},{"time":646000,"text":"This is an ecological network."},{"time":649000,"text":"The flamingos eat the shrimp."},{"time":651000,"text":"The shrimp eat the phytoplankton."},{"time":653000,"text":"So the pinker the belly,"},{"time":655000,"text":"the better the system.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":658000,"text":"Okay, so let's review:"},{"time":660000,"text":"a farm that doesn't feed its animals,"},{"time":663000,"text":"and a farm that measures its success"},{"time":666000,"text":"on the health of its predators."},{"time":668000,"text":"A fish farm, but also a bird sanctuary."},{"time":671000,"text":"Oh, and by the way, those flamingos,"},{"time":673000,"text":"they shouldn't even be there in the first place."},{"time":675000,"text":"They brood in a town"},{"time":677000,"text":"150 miles away,"},{"time":679000,"text":"where the soil conditions"},{"time":681000,"text":"are better for building nests."},{"time":683000,"text":"Every morning, they fly"},{"time":685000,"text":"150 miles into the farm."},{"time":689000,"text":"And every evening, they fly 150 miles back."},{"time":692000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":699000,"text":"They do that because they're able to follow"},{"time":702000,"text":"the broken white line"},{"time":704000,"text":"of highway A92."},{"time":706000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":708000,"text":"No kidding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710000,"text":"I was imagining a \"March of the Penguins\" thing,"},{"time":713000,"text":"so I looked at Miguel."},{"time":715000,"text":"I said, \"Miguel, do they fly"},{"time":717000,"text":"150 miles to the farm,"},{"time":719000,"text":"and then do they fly"},{"time":721000,"text":"150 miles back at night?"},{"time":723000,"text":"Do they do that for the children?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":726000,"text":"He looked at me like I had just quoted a Whitney Houston song."},{"time":729000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":733000,"text":"He said, \"No; they do it because the food's better.\""},{"time":736000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"I didn't mention the skin of my beloved fish,"},{"time":746000,"text":"which was delicious -- and I don't like fish skin;"},{"time":748000,"text":"I don't like it seared, I don't like it crispy."},{"time":751000,"text":"It's that acrid, tar-like flavor."},{"time":755000,"text":"I almost never cook with it."},{"time":758000,"text":"Yet, when I tasted it at that restaurant in southern Spain,"},{"time":761000,"text":"it tasted not at all like fish skin."},{"time":764000,"text":"It tasted sweet and clean,"},{"time":767000,"text":"like you were taking a bite of the ocean."},{"time":770000,"text":"I mentioned that to Miguel, and he nodded."},{"time":772000,"text":"He said, \"The skin acts like a sponge."},{"time":774000,"text":"It's the last defense before anything enters the body."},{"time":777000,"text":"It evolved to soak up impurities.\""},{"time":779000,"text":"And then he added,"},{"time":781000,"text":"\"But our water has no impurities.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":787000,"text":"OK. A farm that doesn't feed its fish,"},{"time":791000,"text":"a farm that measures its success"},{"time":794000,"text":"by the success of its predators."},{"time":796000,"text":"And then I realized when he says,"},{"time":798000,"text":"\"A farm that has no impurities,\""},{"time":801000,"text":"he made a big understatement,"},{"time":803000,"text":"because the water that flows through that farm"},{"time":805000,"text":"comes in from the Guadalquivir River."},{"time":808000,"text":"It's a river that carries with it"},{"time":810000,"text":"all the things that rivers tend to carry these days:"},{"time":813000,"text":"chemical contaminants,"},{"time":815000,"text":"pesticide runoff."},{"time":817000,"text":"And when it works its way through the system"},{"time":820000,"text":"and leaves,"},{"time":822000,"text":"the water is cleaner than when it entered."},{"time":824000,"text":"The system is so healthy, it purifies the water."},{"time":828000,"text":"So, not just a farm that doesn't feed its animals,"},{"time":830000,"text":"not just a farm that measures its success"},{"time":833000,"text":"by the health of its predators,"},{"time":835000,"text":"but a farm that's literally a water purification plant --"},{"time":841000,"text":"and not just for those fish,"},{"time":844000,"text":"but for you and me as well."},{"time":846000,"text":"Because when that water leaves, it dumps out into the Atlantic."},{"time":851000,"text":"A drop in the ocean, I know,"},{"time":853000,"text":"but I'll take it, and so should you,"},{"time":856000,"text":"because this love story,"},{"time":860000,"text":"however romantic,"},{"time":862000,"text":"is also instructive."},{"time":864000,"text":"You might say it's a recipe"},{"time":866000,"text":"for the future of good food,"},{"time":868000,"text":"whether we're talking about bass or beef cattle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872000,"text":"What we need now is"},{"time":874000,"text":"a radically new conception of agriculture,"},{"time":877000,"text":"one in which the food actually tastes good."},{"time":879000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":881000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":887000,"text":"But for a lot people,"},{"time":889000,"text":"that's a bit too radical."},{"time":892000,"text":"We're not realists, us foodies;"},{"time":894000,"text":"we're lovers."},{"time":896000,"text":"We love farmers' markets,"},{"time":898000,"text":"we love small family farms,"},{"time":901000,"text":"we talk about local food,"},{"time":903000,"text":"we eat organic."},{"time":906000,"text":"And when you suggest these are the things"},{"time":908000,"text":"that will ensure the future of good food,"},{"time":912000,"text":"someone, somewhere stands up and says,"},{"time":914000,"text":"\"Hey guy, I love pink flamingos,"},{"time":918000,"text":"but how are you going to feed the world?\""},{"time":921000,"text":"How are you going to feed the world?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":924000,"text":"Can I be honest?"},{"time":926000,"text":"I don't love that question."},{"time":929000,"text":"No, not because we already produce"},{"time":931000,"text":"enough calories to more than feed the world."},{"time":934000,"text":"One billion people will go hungry today."},{"time":937000,"text":"One billion -- that's more than ever before --"},{"time":941000,"text":"because of gross inequalities in distribution,"},{"time":944000,"text":"not tonnage."},{"time":947000,"text":"Now, I don't love this question because it's determined the logic"},{"time":949000,"text":"of our food system for the last 50 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952000,"text":"Feed grain to herbivores,"},{"time":955000,"text":"pesticides to monocultures, chemicals to soil,"},{"time":957000,"text":"chicken to fish,"},{"time":960000,"text":"and all along agribusiness"},{"time":963000,"text":"has simply asked,"},{"time":965000,"text":"\"If we're feeding more people more cheaply,"},{"time":967000,"text":"how terrible could that be?\""},{"time":970000,"text":"That's been the motivation,"},{"time":972000,"text":"it's been the justification:"},{"time":974000,"text":"it's been the business plan"},{"time":977000,"text":"of American agriculture."},{"time":979000,"text":"We should call it what it is:"},{"time":981000,"text":"a business in liquidation,"},{"time":984000,"text":"a business that's quickly eroding"},{"time":987000,"text":"ecological capital that makes that very production possible."},{"time":990000,"text":"That's not a business,"},{"time":992000,"text":"and it isn't agriculture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":994000,"text":"Our breadbasket is threatened today,"},{"time":997000,"text":"not because of diminishing supply,"},{"time":999000,"text":"but because of diminishing resources."},{"time":1002000,"text":"Not by the latest combine and tractor invention,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"but by fertile land;"},{"time":1007000,"text":"not by pumps, but by fresh water;"},{"time":1010000,"text":"not by chainsaws, but by forests;"},{"time":1013000,"text":"and not by fishing boats and nets, but by fish in the sea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1016000,"text":"Want to feed the world?"},{"time":1018000,"text":"Let's start by asking: How are we going to feed ourselves?"},{"time":1022000,"text":"Or better: How can we create conditions"},{"time":1025000,"text":"that enable every community"},{"time":1028000,"text":"to feed itself?"},{"time":1030000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1037000,"text":"To do that,"},{"time":1039000,"text":"don't look at the agribusiness model for the future."},{"time":1042000,"text":"It's really old, and it's tired."},{"time":1044000,"text":"It's high on capital, chemistry and machines,"},{"time":1048000,"text":"and it's never produced anything really good to eat."},{"time":1053000,"text":"Instead, let's look to the ecological model."},{"time":1057000,"text":"That's the one that relies on two billion years"},{"time":1060000,"text":"of on-the-job experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1063000,"text":"Look to Miguel,"},{"time":1065000,"text":"farmers like Miguel."},{"time":1067000,"text":"Farms that aren't worlds unto themselves;"},{"time":1070000,"text":"farms that restore instead of deplete;"},{"time":1075000,"text":"farms that farm extensively"},{"time":1077000,"text":"instead of just intensively;"},{"time":1079000,"text":"farmers that are not just producers,"},{"time":1082000,"text":"but experts in relationships."},{"time":1084000,"text":"Because they're the ones"},{"time":1086000,"text":"that are experts in flavor, too."},{"time":1089000,"text":"And if I'm going to be really honest,"},{"time":1091000,"text":"they're a better chef than I'll ever be."},{"time":1094000,"text":"You know, I'm okay with that,"},{"time":1097000,"text":"because if that's the future of good food, it's going to be delicious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1100000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1102000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}